AGI - Four people died> and thirty others were injured due to a Russian raid against a Kryvyi Rih hotel, > the birthplace of Volodymyr Zelensky, in the Dnipropetrovsk oblast. Governor Serhii Lysak reported it.
A missile hit a five-storey hotel Wednesday night around 22 local time: Initially the news of the death of a 53-year-old man was spread. Lysak then reported that two men and a woman were killed in the attack and a 43-year-old man died in the hospital this morning. Among the wounded, half of which are reported in serious condition, there is a child.
"Since the volunteers of a humanitarian organization have checked in the hotel before the attack: Ukrainian, American and British citizens," said Zelensky. "They survived because they managed to escape from their rooms." Zelensky did not specify if volunteers reported injuries. The missile attack also damaged 14 condominiums, a post office, about two dozen cars, a cultural center and 12 shops, said the governor.
Emergency teams are currently working on the spot to free the site from rubble. The Ukrainian state emergency service said there might be other victims under the rubble. Kryvyi Rih, the birthplace of Zelensky, remains a frequent target of Russian missile attacks. With a population of about 660.000 inhabitants, it is the second largest city of Dnipropetrovsk Oblast, located about 70 kilometers northwest of the nearest front line.&nbsp;
